    rooms: 6.5,
    desc: "Chalet Vetiver is one of Verbier's rare gems, a truly private mountain retreat situated in the picturesque area of Patier \r\n\r\nAs you enter the chalet on the first floor you walk into the main living area which has two set of French Window leading onto the balcony allowing in the stunning viewing towards the Combins range. The separate kitchen in located to the rear of the chalet. \r\n\r\nThe ground floor has two bedrooms with ensuite shower rooms which lead onto the terrace which offers incredible views. There is a sauna and laundry room which rounds off this level. \r\n\r\nLocated on the top floor is a master bedroom with ensuite bathroom and two twin bedrooms sharing a bathroom. \r\n\r\nThere is a garage space for one car, a plethora of storage for ski equipment and a separate WC.\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\nAdditional Information:\r\n\r\nOne of the world's most popular ski destinations, the renowned Alpine resort of Verbier is situated less than 2 hours from Geneva. The resort has become synonymous with high altitude on and off piste skiing, its party atmosphere and year round sporting and cultural activities. It continues to attract an ever increasing international clientele. From its sunny plateau at 1500m, Verbier offers breath-taking views of the Combin Massif and access to the towering heights of Mont Fort. The centre of the resort pulsates with life and there are a wealth of shops, hotels, restaurants, bars and nightclubs to frequent. In winter, Verbier forms the nucleus of the Four Valleys – the largest ski area in Switzerland.\r\n\r\nIn addition to the 410km of groomed pistes, is some of the finest and challenging off -piste in the world. In addition to superb winter sports, Verbier also offers extensive summer activities including mountaineering, paraponting, hiking, golf and mountain biking. Now in its 20th year, Verbier also plays host to the established Verbier Festival in July and August - a 3 week classical music extravaganza. The dual seasonality of the resort ensures a year round vibrancy, not found in many other resorts. Indeed, since 2010, Verbier now has its own International bilingual primary school for pupils aged 3-11.",
